<p>This page offers all the basic information you need about  the cochran's=
 q test. It is part of Statkat=E2=80=99s wiki module, containing similarly =
structured info pages for many different statistical methods. The info page=
s give information about null and alternative hypotheses, assumptions, test=
 statistics and confidence intervals, how to find <i>p </i> values, SPSS ho=
w-to=E2=80=99s and more.</p>
<p>To compare the cochran's q test with other statistical methods, go to St=
atkat's <button class=3D"btn btn-sm btn-success nav-btn" value=3D"../statte=
st.php?t=3D40">Comparison tool</button> or practice with the cochran's q te=
st at Statkat's <button class=3D"btn btn-sm btn-success nav-btn" value=3D".=
./selectquestions.php?s=3D9&amp;m=3D42">Practice question center</button></=
p>

